Team manager for the 'State Development Plan and the Urban Development Plans in Northern Kordofan (Sudan)', on behalf of Mefit Ltd. The plan, commissioned by the Government of Sudan, aims to identify the 'key-projects' for the future 'Five Years Development Plan of Northern Kordofan'
The terms of reference of the assignment specifically concern:
- definition, analysis and implementation of the communication system necessary for the project. The system was created using PHP/MySQL technology, with the use of XML and JavaScript routines, on Apache server;
- assistance in defining the logical framework of the project;
- assistance in defining the team of Sudanese experts;
- training for Sudanese experts on the communication system;
- assistance in defining the plan for carrying out the surveys;
- training for the team of surveyors on how to carry out the surveys;
- control of the carrying out of the surveys and the activities of the team coordinators;
- reception and verification of the periodic reports of the Sudanese team leaders;
- control and verification of the periodic reports of the Italian experts;
- participation in periodic meetings with the Italian experts;
- reception and verification of the final reports of the Italian experts;

Missions to Tunisia on behalf of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs-DGCS for the analysis of a program for the maintenance of cold storage rooms in 41 fishing ports in Tunisia managed by APIP (Agence des ports et installations de pêche), as part of the program Southern Sahara. The terms of reference of the missions specifically concerned:
- the analysis of the current maintenance system in the cold storage rooms managed by APIP;
- the technical analysis (including terms of reference) for the creation of a GMAO software (Gestion de la Maintenance Assistée par Ordinateur);
- the technical analysis of the current IT network, and recommendations for its future development.
